1. create a folder structure as below
Test_Compose
    ├── docker-compose.yml
    ├── java_app
    │   ├── Dockerfile
    │   └── Test_java.java
    ├── python_app
        ├── Dockerfile
        └── test_python.py
        
-> mkdir Test_Compose
-> cd Test_Compose
-> mkdir java_app python_app
-> touch docker-compose.yml
-> touch java_app/Dockerfile java_app/Test_java.java 
-> touch python_app/Dockerfile python_app/test_python.py



2. Enter the appropriate content/code to these files:
->Test_Compose/java_app/Test_java.java:
public class Test_java
{
        public static void main(String args[])
        {
                System.out.println("Hello From Java");
        }
}

->Test_Compose/java_app/Dockerfile:
FROM alpine/java:22-jdk
WORKDIR <path>
COPY Test_java.java .
RUN javac Test_java.java
CMD java Test_java


->Test_Compose/python_app/test_python.py:
print("Hello From Python")


->Test_Compose/python_app/Dockerfile:
FROM python:3.10-slim
WORKDIR <path>
COPY . .
CMD python test_python.py


->Test_Compose/docker-compose.yml:
services:
  java_app:
    build: ./java_app
    container_name: java_container
  python_app:
    build: ./python_app
    container_name: python_container



3.Execute the below command to build the java and python images and run them in different containers using docker compose
-> docker compose up --build
